# rust-doctor — Rust code health scanner

Rust 2024, MSRV 1.85, single crate (not a workspace).

## Commands

```bash
cargo build                        # Debug build (with MCP server)
cargo test                         # All tests
cargo clippy --all-targets -- -W clippy::all -W clippy::pedantic -W clippy::nursery -D warnings
cargo fmt --check
```

## Code Style

- Clippy pedantic enabled
- Custom errors with `thiserror::Error` — no `anyhow`, no `Box<dyn Error>` in library code
- `Result<T, E>` + `?` everywhere — `unwrap()` only in tests
- New passes implement `AnalysisPass` trait, new rules implement `CustomRule` trait
- Diagnostics → stderr, score → stdout

## Boundaries

### Always
- Run `catch_unwind` around custom rules
- MCP tools are read-only — no filesystem writes

### Never
- Use `anyhow` — use typed errors with `thiserror`
- Add `unsafe` blocks in production code
- Break the stderr/stdout output routing
